<br>
Looting while on raids is often times the greatest point of debate during these fun events.  Therefore, the officers of Chivalrous Valor have decided to create a policy that will be in effect for all future Chivalrous Valor lead raids.  This policy is non-negotiable and is in effect as of 3/1/03.<br>
<br>
I. Overview<br>
<br>
Our looting policy is somewhat complex in that it is based on a hybrid of need before greed and point system looting.  It has been our experience that this type of structure encourages raid participation and eliminates hard feelings due to hours of hard work and potential deaths with no chance of looting.<br>
<br>
II. Looters<br>
<br>
The only players capable of looting on Chivalrous Valor lead raids are the Raid Leader and one raid leader selected individual in each group.<br>
<br>
III. Loot Distribution<br>
<br>
All advanced items (typically items that can be equipped) will be distributed based on NBG and point based random rolls at the completion of the raid.  If you do not attend the post raid looting event, you have no claim to any of the loot.  Post raid looting events will begin no later than 15 minutes post raid completion.<br>
<br>
For non-advanced items, (typically items that cannot be equipped or items with low stats), these items will be sold to the nearest vendor at the post raid looting event.  All monies received from such sales will be held by the raid leader for spell component reimbursement and to fund future raids.<br>
<br>
IV. Need before greed<br>
<br>
For all advanced items, in order to qualify for the random roll at the post raid looting event, you *must* be able to equip the item and the item must be superior to the item you currently have equipped in that slot.  <br>
<br>
EXCEPTION: Epic pieces are exempt from this policy.  Please see the section entitled Epic Pieces for detailed looting policies.<br>
<br>
V. Point based rolling<br>
<br>
As stated before, you have the opportunity to gain two raid points per raiding event.  You must have at least one raid point in the point bank and a *need* for the item to be eligible for the roll.  Regardless of a win or a loss on the roll, a single point will be deducted from your point bank.  Raid points will be posted on the Chivalrous Valor message board within 24 hours post raid.<br>
<br>
EXCEPTION: Epic pieces are exempt from this policy.  Please see the section entitled Epic Pieces for detailed looting policies.<br>
<br>
VI. Epic Pieces<br>
<br>
Epic pieces will be awarded to the player that is furthest along in their epic progress.  If two or more players are at the same progress point in their epic quest, the epic piece will be awarded based on a random roll between those players.  Winning of an epic piece roll will cost you 75% of the raid points available in your bank.  The loss of a roll on an epic piece will cost you 1 raid point.<br>
<br>
EXCEPTION: Chivalrous Valor members and their allies will have priority on epic pieces regardless of progress in their epic quest.  If two or more members of Chivalrous Valor or Chivalrous Valor's allies require a single epic piece, a random roll will occur between those players.<br>
